        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 7:23PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 723 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Grenora, or 23 miles southeast of Plentywood, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dagmar and Coalridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
